item.column: We are devoted to maintaining a continuing dialog between all people who believe in the basic goodness of human nature without supernaturalism. 21st Century Humanism fosters the preservation and growth of Humanism, freedom of thought, freedom of expression, separation of church and state, and the traditional Humanist values of reason, rationality, experience, and the scientific method in a post 9/11 world by examining the real problems of humanists, agnostics, atheists, relativists, freethinkers, rationalists, skeptics, and others.

Located in Little Rock, the ASoF has the largest membership within the Central Arkansas CoR. It was founded in 1994 and merged with other local atheist, agnostic, and humanist groups in 2008 to form the very active group we have today.
To bring together all those who think freely.
We are a group of people tied together by our shared non-belief in god or gods (aka Atheism).
Adat Chaverim, Congregation for Humanistic Judaism
Adat Chaverim is a Humanistic Jewish Congregation offering a non-theistic supportive community that promotes pluralism, inclusion, and cultural continuity for our children.
The Advocates for Freethought and Skepticism is an Oregon State recognized student group.
African American Humanist Society, Baltimore, MD

A group for African-American Atheists, Agnostics, Secular Humanists, Skeptics, and all those who are living good lives without belief in a God or gods. Our purpose is to discuss the role African Americans with secular views play in society.

African Americans for Humanism DC (AAH DC) exists to bring these secular humanists together, to provide a forum for communication, and to facilitate coordinated action. In an irrational world, those who stand for reason must stand together.
Agnostic and Atheist Student Association (at UC Davis)

The Agnostic and Atheist Student Association, or AgASA is a campus organization with the purpose of uniting the many agnostics, secularists, skeptics, and atheists on campus and providing an opportunity to socialize with like-minded individuals, while questioning religious and theistic beliefs. The club is predominantly made up of people who identify as materialists/naturalists/physicalists (people who do not believe in any form of the supernatural) and non-theists who believe in some things that are supernatural. However, everyone is welcome to the general meetings and to partake in the discussions.

We are a high school group that wishes to have a meeting place on campus so that we may educate and empower the community of non-believers; adult and student and help to educate the community about Non-believers (atheist, agnostics, skeptics, etc.) and why the stereotypes given to us are wrong.
Air Capital Skeptics (SkeptITC), Wichita State University

Air Capital Skeptics is a group of critical thinkers who get together to talk, eat, drink, and promote critical thinking skills. Myths, legends, and pseudoscience pose an increasing threat to our modern society. By promoting the use of the scientific method as the way to examine the world around us rather than relying on superstition we can ensure that we continue to have a bright future. For our adult members we host Skeptics in the Pub events where we can eat, drink, and be skeptical. For our younger members (and adults!) we host Skeptics in the Park where we can also eat, drink, and perform the kind of science experiments that you aren\'t allowed to do indoors. Occasionally we may host special events and presentations.
We are the Crimson Secular Student Alliance. We are the primary free-thinking and non-religious organization at the University of Alabama!

This group will support, foster, and nurture parents and children in Alamance County (and surrounding areas) who are not religious (agnostic, atheist, humanist, etc...). Our aim is to introduce free-thinkers to other free-thinkers, in the hopes their children will find comfort and support in having like-minded friends. We encourage compassion, respect, kindness, and civility in all interactions and with persons of any and every background or affiliation.

This is a social group for Atheists and Agnostics. Our members may also identify as Non-Religious, Skeptics, Humanists, Freethinkers, Naturalists, Rationalists, Secularists and others. Whether we agree or respectfully disagree, we seek to form friendships and build our own community through fellowship.

Albany Georgia Atheists is an accessible and inclusive community of atheists, agnostics, secular humanists, skeptics, and other freethinkers in the Albany area with the goals of building a social network for atheists and other non-believers for the promotion of the atheist perspective and to remove the stigma that is commonly attached to religious non-belief.
Alliance of Happy Atheists (AHA - Univ. of Oregon)

The Alliance of Happy Atheists (AHA!) was formed by nonreligious University of Oregon students in early 2009. As an officially recognized student organization accepted by the Associated Students at the University of Oregon, we are a group of over 300 atheists, agnostics, secularists, and allies dedicated to changing the image of atheism, promoting critical thinking, and having a great time while we are at it!
Alliance of Happy Atheists at Cal Poly San Luis Obispo
The Cal Poly Alliance of Happy Atheists (AHA!). The only club for secular students at Cal Poly San Luis Obispo.
Allied Non-Believers United- The Reality Union
Allied Non-Believers United is an umbrella organization to allow all non-believers of the supernatural and religious cultural myth to have one registry to represent us.
A gathering of Atheists, Agnostics, Humanists, and Secularists at Alma College. Join for updates on events, meetings, or just good old fashioned discussion.

This group is open to people who live and work on Ft Meade/NSA (Active Duty and Civilian) and their families and military members who live in the Fort Meade area. Membership is extended to atheists, non-theists and humanists. The group is a safe place for us to discuss issues that relate to us and to atheism.
Americans United for Separation of Church and State - San Diego

Americans United is a nonpartisan educational organization dedicated to preserving the constitutional principle of church-state separation. The primary mission of the San Diego Chapter is to provide a grassroots presence for the education and advocacy work of the national organization and to actively defend religious liberty in the local community.
Animal Loving Agnostic Dorks of SGV
The purpose of this group is to have meetups where like-minded people can make new friends, experience fun things, and have intellectual conversations.
Socializing for atheists, freethinkers and anyone interested in a godless good time.

Do you have a rational worldview based on the natural world? Do you seek ethical models based on reason and compassion? Do you have an affinity and respect for science and skepticism? Are you looking to meet others like you in one of the most religiously conservative corners of California? Then please check us out!

Calling all AHS Agnostics, Atheists, Free-thinkers, Humanists, ect. (any religion is welcome and we do encourage people of any faith to come and share their thoughts). Not only is this a club geared towards discussion, but we\'ll also be doing community service and volunteering, if you\'re interested!

AA/AA is the Appalachian Agnostic/Atheist Association. We are a service organization, a network of support for atheists/agnostics, and a discussion group dedicated to exploring the vast array of issues related to non-belief and skeptical analysis. This group promotes reasonable tolerance, mutual understanding, and a courteous exchange of ideas. We are nationally affiliated with the Secular Students\' Alliance. Membership to this group is open ONLY to individuals affiliated with Appalachian State University. After requesting permission to join, you may be asked to verify your affiliation.

The Unitarian Universalist Fellowship of Mobile values freedom, responsibility, acceptance of others without judgment, world community, and respect for the entire interconnected web of existence. UUFM is a church without dogma and we have members with a variety of backgrounds and religious perspectives.
Secular Student Alliance of Arkansas Tech
Arkansas Tech University chapter of the Secular Student Alliance. This is a very informal group where we discuss anything relevant to the secular community.

Asheville Skeptics (ASk) is dedicated to promoting the use of scientific skepticism & critical thinking. Our meetings are for people interested in skeptical inquiry, current events in science, state & church separation, and medicine. We support critical evaluation of alternative health modalities, conspiracy claims, and pseudoscience in general.
Association Humaniste du Quebec (Humanist Association of Quebec)
Association Humaniste du Quebec (Humanist Association of Quebec)

The Association of Humanistic Rabbis (AHR) was founded in 1967 by rabbis committed to the values and teachings of a humanistic perspective in Jewish life. The purpose of the AHR is to support the values of the movement of Secular Humanistic Judaism, a human-centered approach to Jewish life and culture. AHR members are dedicated to promoting the on-going learning, fellowship and welfare of its members.
Conoce a otros locales de los ateos, librepensadores y humanistas. Se reúnen para discutir las creencias y filosofías, y hacer nuevos amigos.
Welcoming the skeptical, doubting, the curious, the logical, and the adamant alike!

We strongly advocate activism, including rallies and speaking at government meetings on issues of vital importance to atheists and freethinkers. We certainly welcome atheists and freethinkers who want to socialize at picnics and have discussions at educational meetings without getting more active. We will continue to organize such events, as we have done in the past, but are convinced that we must go beyond meetings and dinners to activism in order to affect change.
We are an atheist organization that was formed in 2005 at the University of Texas at San Antonio.

The Atheist Coalition of San Diego was formed in 1991 and is a not for profit group which holds monthly meetings and other events. The primary objectives and purposes are: 1) To promote separation of government and religions, which means to educate the public about the value of secular government, alert the community to government / religion separation violations, and work in all lawful ways to ensure separation of governments and religions. 2) To promote atheism, which means to educate and inform the public about atheism, presenting it as a worth-while, life affirming, and wholesome point of view, protect the civil and constitutional rights of atheists, clarify and explain atheist ideas for atheists and non-atheists, and develop opportunities for atheists to learn more about each other. 3) To coordinate activities with other groups to achieve common goals and objectives, in affiliations which do no compromise the autonomy of the Atheist Coalition.

We are a group of like-minded people who enjoy doing a variety of activities together. We are open and welcoming to all. If you are an Atheist, Freethinker, Humanist, Skeptic, or Agnostic and enjoy doing activity such as potluck socials, night life, karaoke, hikes, volunteerism, meetings with speakers, music concerts, secular bible study or just about any activity with secular friends, you have come to the right meetup group. We like to focus on community service and giving back to the community. We volunteer at community based secular and non-secular non-profit organizations and events several times a month.
Meet other local atheists, freethinkers and heathens. Gather to discuss worldviews and philosophies, and make new friends.

These days we\'re a social group. Many of us are comfortable being called atheists. Some aren\'t, preferring the agnostic title. (Though I don\'t think any of the atheists consider themselves gnostic.) Honestly though, we don\'t care what belief you bring to the table as long as you don\'t expect us to except it without evidence that has been properly examined. (Which probably means peer review.) Anyway, we get together in friendly, open gatherings without agenda or forethought.

Our mission is simple: bring the local non-theist community together in a warm, welcoming way, where every member can speak openly and honestly about his or her lack of belief in supreme beings or deities without being judged and without the fear of reprisal or condemnation from society at large.
Meet other local atheists, freethinkers and infidels. Gather to discuss beliefs and philosophies, and make new friends.

The Atheist Community of Tulsa is made up of average every day people; your co-workers, family, friends, neighbors, even open minded churchgoers. We are very friendly and like to talk openly with other like-minded people without the fear of persecution. We are non-discriminatory and welcome people of all ethnicity, age, sexual orientation, and beliefs.

Greetings! This group is for atheists, etc. -- including agnostics, skeptics, freethinkers, secular humanists, and other non-religious individuals -- who are interested in meeting like-minded people and having engaging discussions. Most of our events are in the northeast suburbs of Indianapolis (including Noblesville, Fishers, Fortville and Castleton), but we also post events for similar groups in the Indianapolis area, such as Indy Atheists and CFI Indiana.
The Atheist Families of San Antonio provides a healthy social environment for families of atheists, agnostics, skeptics, humanists, freethinkers and other non-believers.
We decided to start the group because it is hard to find people who are happy to share their intellect and perspectives on being atheist.
Atheist group of non-religious, non-superstitious, freethinking individuals.

The Atheist Scholar is an online academic resource for those interested in the serious, interdisciplinary study of atheism. The Atheist Scholar provides a comprehensive overview for the student of atheism, a review of the best books on atheism, and summaries of literature and movies of interest to atheists.

This is the facebook group of the Atheist Society (of Salisbury, formerly known as ASS). The Atheist Society aims to foster understanding and appreciation of atheism, agnosticism, naturalism, and secularism, to provide a forum for discussion, to encourage dialogue between theists and non-theists, and to provide a social support network among non-theists.

The purpose of the Atheist Student Alliance is to provide a sense of community to atheists, agnostics, and their allies. We aim build a supportive, social community where students that may cultivate friendships and discussion. We also hope to abolish the stigma associated with being an atheist by raising awareness about atheism throughout the Rutgers community.
The Atheist Student Alliance (ASA) is a student organization at the University of South Florida with the purpose of promoting fellowship and understanding among our members and the USF community.
The purpose of our organization will be to educate college students on matters relating to atheism, agnosticism, skeptical thinking, non-theism, humanism, rationalism, and secular thinking.

In a traditional Bible study, the purpose is to discover God\'s word through the text. Our approach is different: we regard each text as a lens into the past. For our meet-ups, we use a selected text of the Hebrew and Christian scriptures to generate conversation about history, religion, literature, contemporary society, and even arts and sciences. This group is based in Greenville, SC.
Atheist and Agnostic Parents of Maple Valley
This group was started to help Atheist/Agnostic families in the Maple Valley, Black Diamond, Ravensdale, Hobart, and Covington areas find each other.

The Atheist/Agnostic Parent of Seattle meetup is designed to support the freethought communities in the Puget Sound region by providing nonreligious parents a place where they can meet other parents who share their outlook and values. We will strive to provide regular biweekly outings around the area that will encourage our children to learn and play together. We are also committed to providing moral, ethical and emotional support to ourselves, our children and our community.
This is the official meetup group for the Lakeland chapter of Atheists & Humanists of Florida. Everyone is invited to attend our regular monthly meetings, which are open to the public.

This is the official meetup group for the Atheists and Humanists of Florida. Everyone is invited to attend our regular meetings, which are open to the public, and we encourage you to keep in touch with local area events.
Atheists and Agnostics Group of Rossmoor
The Atheists and Agnostics Group of Rossmoor is a group of atheists and agnostics in retirement community in Walnut Creek, CA.
Atheists and Freethinkers of Denver is a Denver-based group with an eclectic group of secularists, rationalists, humanists, skeptics, agnostics, and atheists.
This is the official meetup group for the Atheists and Humanists of Florida.

The purpose of the association, Atheists and Other Freethinkers, is to promote the civic understanding of atheism and the acceptance of atheists in our community. Through educational programs, projects, and publications, AOF will extend secular perspectives, including the separation of religion and government and the right to think and speak freely on these perspectives.

We are a group of students interested in maintaining an OU Atheist organization to create an engaging and ongoing conversation on the importance of science and reason in a world dominated by dangerous religious dogma.

Many atheists often closet themselves. It may feel that being true to your own beliefs will cause your family or friends to alienate you because of their misconceptions. Overall, we aim to eradicate these misconceptions and prejudices about atheism, while engaging members in the ideas of science, reason, and humanism. There is a place for you. We feel that religiosity is often intertwined within one’s life through society and culture, and therefore it is often difficult to “come out” as atheist (or non-theist or non-religious) or discuss your philosophical views with others. Primarily, we hope to provide a safe haven for fellow atheists. We will provide resources about science, reason, and religious philosophy. Club activities will include community service, education, riveting (we hope) discussions, and fundraising to bring some great speakers to the Ball State campus.

This group is to provide atheists in DC with an opportunity to get to know each other. We don\'t necessarily have to talk about our deep philosophical thoughts on life (although we can if we want). It is simply a chill way to meet folks with a similar interest and have some organized fun in DC.
A group for those in the Binghamton area that do not believe in God (or any other unproven forms of magic/spirituality) and wish to socialize with like-minded infidels.

This group is for Atheists, Free thinkers, Agnostics, and Humanists to get together and socialize as well as discuss topics that affect us as non-believers however, anyone is welcome as long as you are respectful.

Why we are here? We would like to see a world where public places, public education and public policies were not being shaped by what religionists think their god commands. To sit by and watch this happen is no longer an option. As concerned members of our north state community we are coming together to be active citizens in the conversations about how we live our lives, both public and private. We direct our lives not an unseen power. You can have your own opinions but not your own facts.
A networking, social group for the Central Ohio area humanists, skeptics, atheists, agnostics, nonbelievers, freethinkers, and the curious.

This is a social meetup for the Port Richey area in Pasco County. Our mission is to: advance the cause of atheism and atheists by advocacy and action concerning the separation of church and state; promote education about atheism within our group and the community; improve the image of atheists through public relations.

This is a meetup for Atheists of Sarasota. We unite a community of activists to uphold the complete and absolute separation of church and state. Our mission is to: advance the cause of atheism and atheists by advocacy and action concerning the separation of church and state; promote education about atheism within our group and the community; improve the image of atheists through public relations.
West Kennedy Boulevard, Tampa, FL, USA
Atheists of Florida unites a community of activists to uphold the complete and absolute separation of church and state.
Meet and organize with other Atheists!
Atheists of Santa Cruz and Monterey Counties
A group for non-believers no matter the label--atheist, agnostic, humanist, freethinker, etc.
Atheists of the New River Valley

Atheists of the New River Valley is an organization for people interested in atheism, equal rights for atheists and issues related to the separation of church and state. Some atheists refer to themselves as rationalists, humanists, secularists, freethinkers, etc. All are welcome in this group.

We exist to defend and promote the separation of church and state, educate the public about non-theists and church-state separation, enrich and empower our membership through education and awareness, and provide a social and intellectual community for freethinkers.
Atheists of Utah Zion Sect, Salt Lake City

Atheists of Utah (AOU) is an independent, democratically-run, non-profit membership organization. Our main objective is to provide a social community where non-theists can come together and mingle with other like-minded people.
We are a major community for atheists in the greater Los Angeles area.

If you are interested in meeting local SFV atheists and freethinkers for conversation and friendship, this is the group to join! We are a fun group, with some very great people. Our group will give you the sense of community that you might be seeking in your atheistic life! We welcome atheists, agnostics, brights, freethinkers, rationalists, humanists of any flavor, and anyone else who embraces reason and a naturalistic view of the universe.

Do you have a rational worldview based on the natural world? Do you seek ethical models in the world that are based on compassion, science, and empiricism? Do you have an affinity and respect for science and skepticism? Are you looking to meet others who share your worldview in one of the most religiously conservative corners of California? Then come check us out!

This group is for families of atheists, freethinkers, humanists, agnostics and all others with a rational world view with a focus on planning family-friendly activities and providing rational parents with a place to share and learn about raising freethinking children.

Established in 1982, Atheists United is a 501(c)(3) not-for-profit, tax deductible educational organization. We are one of the largest freethought organizations in the nation and the largest in the Southern California area. As an affiliate of Atheists Alliance of America and the Los Angeles Freethought Federation, Atheists United is committed to consolidating the collective efforts of its members to affect change on a local, national and international level to advance the cause of an atheist community, secular government and religious tolerance.
By providing regularly planned events and the opportunity for fellowship, Atheists United hopes to inspire a vibrant and active atheist community. For far too many non-believers, isolation is a common experience as religious belief tends to be an assumed default, discouraging those who might abide by their freedom of conscience to admit their doubt or non-belief. Atheists United provides a welcoming environment where atheists can meet and are encouraged to connect with other non-believers.

Atheists United SLO is a meeting place for all atheists, humanists, rationalists, skeptics, doubters, agnostics, and other non-believers to get to know each other, share ideas and build a community of like-minded individuals in San Luis Obispo County.
Atheists, Agnostics and Freethinkers at NYU
AAF at NYU is a discussion-based student group dedicated to raising awareness and promoting critical thinking about secular issues in America and the world.
Atheists, Agnostics and Secular Humanists at Nazareth (AASH@Naz)
AASH-Atheist, Agnostic, Secular Humanist community at Nazareth College.
Atheists, Agnostics, and Freethinkers of Waterloo

Atheists, Agnostics, and Freethinkers of Waterloo (AAFW) aims to create an open atmosphere for the exchange of ideas and debates of current events in a safe forum, from the perspective of atheists, agnostics, and freethinkers.

A³ is a student group geared towards discussing secular world views, challenging conceptions, promoting tolerance, encouraging skepticism, and a fostering a better general understanding of secular philosophy and the sciences.
While A³ is mainly for atheists, agnostics, and secular humanists, we are open to people of varying beliefs who have questions and wish to learn more about what and who we are.
Atheists, Humanists and Agnostics (AHA!) at the UW-Madison
The mission of Atheists, Humanists, & Agnostics at the UW-Madison shall be to promote the discussion of faith and religion on the UW-Madison campus.
Atheists, Humanists and Agnostics at LSU
Atheists, Humanists and Agnostics at LSU
Atheists, Humanists, and Agnostics at Stanford (AHA!)
Atheists, Humanists, and Agnostics (AHA!) at Stanford is a joint graduate-undergraduate student organization that promotes freethought and rational discourse on the Stanford campus.
Atheists, Humanists, and Skeptics of Bozeman
AHS is a group dedicated to improving the overall image of atheism in society as well as providing a community for non-believers of all types.
Atheists, Skeptics, and Humanists at UTD
The official group for Atheists, Skeptics, and Humanists at UTD, an Affiliate of the Secular Student Alliance.

The Atlanta Freethought Society is a 501(c)(3) non-profit educational organization that exists to provide a community for non-theists in the Metro Atlanta, Georgia area through educational, advocacy, and social activities.
Had enough of astrologers, psychics, homeopaths, and spirit channelers? Yearning to talk with someone rational for awhile? Meetup with other local skeptics for some refreshing and sane conversation.

The purpose of this club is as follows: First, to educate and promote debate on atheism and skepticism, while promoting science as the ideal rational method of inquiry for discovering facts about our universe. Second, to promote the secularization of the United States Government, as was the intention of the Founding Fathers. Third, to remove the social stigma associated with atheism by opening lines of dialogue on atheism and religion and the differences between the two. Finally, to promote a social and welcoming environment for those questioning their beliefs and who face societal pressures to follow an established religion.

Freethinkers, humanists, skeptics, agnostics, atheist and all non-believers are welcome! A meeting of minds where we can share ideas, ask questions, teach, learn and grow, benefiting from each others life stories and thoughts. Our meetings are very informal and friendly. We meet at least once a month but we also have other gatherings throughout the year. In addition, we are in contact with other freethought groups in the Seattle/Tacoma area and we enjoy going to their events as well. There is always something happening in this awesome community of ours.
Auburn University Montgomery Secular Student Alliance

The Auburn University Montgomery Secular Student Alliance is an opportunity for Skeptics, Atheists, Agnostics, and Freethinkers to collaborate and share their thoughts with other like-minded individuals. This is a place for the aforementioned AUM students to communicate and plan events.

Auraria Campus Atheists (previously Metro State Atheists) is an affiliate of The Center for Inquiry (CFI); Which is an international not-for-profit umbrella organization uniting freethinking, skeptic, secularist, atheist/agnostic, and humanist students and student organizations

Backyard Skeptics is one of the most active groups with six chapters and over 1000 members. We meet monthly in Villa Park (next to the city of Orange) usually on the fourth Wednesday or Thursday. You can freely talk about just about atheism, skepticism or any philosophy on non-belief. Only one person talks at a time so everyone can hear, (unlike a noise restaurant) and we usually have a topic or speaker for each meeting. We also have diner-and-a-movie night, field trips, and join forces with other groups for exciting events.
Our goal: To support the atheist/agnostic/skeptic and humanist community with local meetings, potluck parties, and other events. To educate the public that non-believers are part of the community and are good and moral people. We cherish humanistic values over any supernatural superstitions and are good without God. We encourage and educate others to look at their worldview with critical thinking skills.

Our goal: To support the atheist/agnostic/skeptic/humanist community with local meetings, potluck parties, and other social events. To spread the word that skeptics and non-believers are good and moral people and to promote secular values and the separation of church and state. We cherish humanistic values over any supernatural superstitions and encourage others to look at their worldview with critical thinking skills.

This group is for skeptics of all types. You might say a skeptic is one who is an evidential truth-seeker an evidencialist. One who knows what his/her reality is by the evidence presented to them. One who inquirers about everything, but accepts the most reasonable explanation based on science and falsifiable claims
Seeking secular, naturalistic dialogue and discourse here in South Orange County, CA?
Our group promotes science, reason, and free exchange of ideas.
A member society of the American Ethical Union.
The Chavurah is a secular humanistic Jewish community and is affiliated with the Congress of Secular Jewish Organizations and the Society for Humanistic Judaism.
We believe in raising our kids to be ethical and caring freethinkers and to teach them values of reason and compassion. We welcome families of humanists, atheists, freethinkers, skeptics.
BSH is a discussion group for exploring issues about morality, science, and society for WASH members or other interested people in the greater Baltimore, MD, area.
This Meetup is a place to join others who are willing to question and challenge cherished dogmas of any stripe.
Meet like-minded blasphemers around the Bay.
If you are interested in establishing an active Humanist organization in San Francisco and the East Bay, please join this Meetup.

The organization encourages critical thinking and accuracy in the media and in our schools. We encourage rational thought and critical thinking through the use of scientific methods. We are particularly interested in such topics as claims of the paranormal, pseudoscience, and untested or poorly tested medical and psychotherapeutic practices. BAS is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization.
The BC Humanist Association has provided a community for secular humanists, atheists, and freethinkers in Vancouver for over 25 years.

An affiliate of the BC Humanist Association, the Oceanside Humanists represents atheists, agnostics, secular humanists, skeptics, and other freethinkers on Vancouver Island. Communities served include: Nanaimo, Parksville, Qualicum Beach, and everywhere in between.

BE. Orlando is a secular group offering opportunities for engagement in positive social and volunteer activities and promoting equality and inclusivity. In addition to regular events, major initiatives include focused needs drives, PintClub (a blood donor challenge), and a Volunteers Beyond Belief team.

Beltway Atheists Inc. is a 501(c)(3) corporation located in Leesburg, VA. It supports and promotes nonpartisan activities to increase public awareness of matters relating to the separation of church and state.
An informal philosophy group with discussions focused on readings selected by participating members.
Beth Ami, Colorado Congregation for Humanistic Judaism

Beth Ami provides the opportunity to celebrate Jewish culture and identity consistent with a humanistic philosophy of life. Humanistic Judaism offers a Secular alternative in contemporary Jewish life, and is compatible with many belief systems. This congregation meets in a variety of places in the greater Denver-Boulder area.
Beth Chaverim is a Humanistic Jewish community.

Based in Billings, Montana, the Billings Association of Humanists formed in 2003. It is a Charter Chapter of the American Humanist Association.
The purpose of the Billings Association of Humanists is a to promote Humanism; an ethical, democratic, naturalistic lifestance that: challenges irrationality, promotes critical thinking and the separation of church and state. We present a system of Humanist ethics that is a rational alternative to those based in religion and encourage fellowship among thoughtful people in our community.
The Birmingham Temple provides Jewish education, celebration and community as part of the world movement of Humanistic Judaism.

The purpose of this group is not to separate us from other freethinkers. It is to change the perception that being a person of color (POC) automatically means you believe in the supernatural. It’s to provide support. We can and do lead positive, fulfilling lives without a higher power.

The Black Hills Freethinkers are a not-for-profit group located beneath Mount Rushmore, the Shrine of Democracy, in Rapid City, SD. We seek to provide a community for non-theists, promote education and critical thought in the local area, and provide opportunities for people to participate in giving back to the community and protecting the wall of separation and our secular Constitution locally and nationally.

BN is a non-profit fellowship of nonbelievers in the Atlanta area that is dedicated to providing an informative, caring, festive and family friendly environment. We strive to connect with other Blacks (and their allies) who are living free of religion and irrational beliefs, and might otherwise be shunned by family and friends. Instead of accepting dogma, we seek to determine truth and morality through reason and evidence. BN welcomes all regardless of sex, sexuality, gender identity, age, national origin or race. We extend a caring embrace to all who wish to participate in exploring a meaningful rational life.

Our group exists so that black nonbelievers and our allies can get together from time to time for rational discussions, fun, and laid-back secular fellowship. Our overall goal is to create camaraderie, support, and friendship among black nonbelievers of diverse backgrounds.

Black Secular Society is a group that aims to gather great minds together for activities that nurture our minds, bodies and community. Located in the DC, Maryland, Virginia Metro area, we hope to bring local members of the Black secular community together and provide a safe haven for individuals and their families to openly express their freedom from doctrine.

Black Skeptics Los Angeles (BSLA) is a 501(c)3 nonprofit organization dedicated to providing Humanist public education, media representation, and cultural resources for African American non-believers and their allies.

The Bloomington-Normal Freethinkers is open to anyone interested in atheism. Our objectives include: fostering awareness and reaching out to religiously skeptical people in our community, being a source of community and group support, stimulating the intellect of fellow group members, supporting larger (i.e. regional, national) groups with similar goals, and participating as humanists in community service.
Bon Vivant Social Club of Tampa

Basically, we are the people living in the Boston Metropolitan area (extending into New Hampshire and Rhode Island) who believe in Humanism and try to live a Humanistic life and who like to get together in association with each other in formal or informal humanistically oriented activities.

Had enough of junk science, pseudo-science, astrologers, psychics, homeopaths, and spirit channelers? Yearning to talk with someone rational for awhile? Meetup with other local skeptics, science promoters, rationalists, and critical thinkers for some refreshing and sane conversation, and to work toward making a difference in a community often overly informed by irrational influences.

Open now to serve the Greater L.A. skeptical community... east side, west side, downtown, uptown, San Fernando and San Gabriel valleys -- hopefully there will be something for everyone! Had enough of astrologers, psychics, homeopaths, and bible thumpers? Yearning to talk with someone rational for awhile? Meet up with other L.A.-based skeptics for some refreshing and sane conversation and some great activities. No sacred cows here--just an ever-growing community of critical thinkers willing to raise their voices and exchange ideas.

The Greater Lowell Area Skeptics Society (GLASS) was started to help foster a healthy community of critical thinkers who gather to talk, eat, drink, game, and whatever else we do to be fun and social. We hold up the candle of science to shine light on the darkness of all things pseudo-scientific.

We are a community of Freethinkers who represent logical reason against the religious minded in Alabama. We believe decisions for Alabama should be based on human needs and not religious faith. We are a Secular Free thinking group, and other similar systems of thought are welcome.

Greater Worcester Humanists is an active chapter of the American Humanist Association. We provide a welcoming environment and a range of activities for area humanists and those interested in learning more about humanism. We have regular meetings, guest speakers, movie screenings, discussions of timely topics, and social activities, etc. We also celebrate humanist holidays such as Darwin Day, Freethought Day, Human Light, and the National Day of Reason. Most of our meetings are free and open to the public.

The Greensboro Atheists Organization is a community for non-believers to make connections, to come out to friends and family, or to have simple conversations without the fear of being judged, attacked, or face repercussions. GAO is a place to not only connect with other intelligent people with similar thoughts and beliefs, but to be free of fear, be able to have logical discussions, and deal with what faces us in our day to day lives including personally, politically, and in the whole scheme of things.

Greenville Tech Freethought Organization (GTFO) This group is for students of Greenville Technical College that are looking for a code of ethics and morals that affirms the inherent dignity and worth of every human being, without invoking the supernatural. We are dedicated to the search for meaning and values on this earth through reliance on intelligence and the scientific method, democracy and social sympathy.
If you find religion somewhat lacking, faith a little too unjustified or just find belief unbelievable, then Humanism may be just what you are looking for.
A Meetup group for Agnostics, Atheists, Freethinkers, Humanists, Skeptics, and other similar minded people based around Pensacola, Florida.

We are Charter Members of the American Humanist Association and a subchapter of the Humanists of Florida Association. The Gulf Coast Humanist Association has been serving the Venice, Englewood, North Port and Port Charlotte communities since 2004.

Meet other local people whose worldview is naturalistic. We have regular monthly meetings in Gwinnett for Secularists, Humanists, Brights, Skeptics, Naturalists, Non-believers, Rationalists, Infidels, Non-theists, Freethinkers, Atheists, Agnostics, Normals.
Gwinnett Rationals for Reason, Georgia Gwinnett College

The Gwinnett Rationals for Reason is a group of skeptics, scientists, atheists, agnostics, and secular humanists whose common goal is to establish a home at GGC for freethinking students. We aim to improve our knowledge of the sciences, to understand viewpoints which differ from our own, and to create an environment where ideas flow freely, but are subject to logical, evidence-based criticism.

Where every day is a good day to be human. This group is a place for Humanists of all stripes from the Hampton Roads area, offering a place for socializing and information about relevant news, local events, and activism opportunities.
Meet other local atheists and freethinkers for conversation and friendship! Join us for an informal dinner to discuss beliefs, philosophies, and religious influence in America.

H-PHC welcomes freethinking individuals, atheists and humanists concerned with the incursion of religion into civic affairs. We hope you find us to be a forum where you will be able to express your views, freely, among other atheists.

Meet other local atheists, agnostics, secular humanists, freethinkers, infidels, heathens and pastafarians. Gather to discuss philosophy, science, religion, politics, ethics, etc and make new friends.

This group is a special interest group of the Washington Area Secular Humanists for people in the Harford County area. We are interested in freethought, skepticism about religious and supernatural claims, discussion of current events, and philosophy and ethics.

Harris County Democratic Socialists is a community for those interested in the topics of socialism, communism, syndicalism, and other economic alternatives to capitalism. We are primarily a social organization facilitating friendship, learning, and consciousness raising, but have many members involved in community and political organizing if that interests you as well. If you are in the Houston area and are interested in freely discussing alternatives to the capitalist ideology, come on out and meet with a great group of like-minded people.
The goal of our little group is to provide Harrisburg area nonbelievers with the useful social and culture services usually fulfilled by churches.
This group is for the atheist ladies! Come on out and join us for a couple of drinks and good discussion.
The purpose of this group is to bring atheists together and build a community of like-minded people for support, education and fun.

The purpose of this group is to offer education about the many different topics of interest to skeptics and non-believers in the Washington DC area as well as for those who like to read on science, humanism, atheism and resources that encourage rationalism. We seek to create a conscience about religious deception and all un-natural beliefs, helping to increment critical and skeptic thinking providing a community space for freethinkers. We believe a society without dogmas is an important part for societal human development and future generations.

This will be a group for study, for discussion, for discovery and perhaps even creation of ideas. It is for those who value novelty, creativity, cleverness, wit, words, honesty, skepticism, inquiry, and intelligence in all its forms. We who eschew dogmatism, authority, institutions, rules, and other societal-bio-evolutionary pressures in order that we may attempt to think for ourselves.
Located in Hot Springs, the Hot Springs Freethinkers goal is to promote a society that is guided by natural laws and reason rather than the supernatural and superstition.

The Houston Atheists is a growing group of freethinking people who have come together as a community to offer its members opportunities for social networking, education, and community service. Every month we have a full calendar of activities all over Houston and the surrounding areas, including educational seminars, dinners, coffee socials, happy hour gatherings, star-gazing events, holiday parties, movies, sports/games, hiking and camping, as well as kid-friendly family get-togethers at the zoo, museum, and beach.
This group was started as a way for atheists in the Hudson Valley to meet.
The Freethinkers of the Hudson Valley strive to replace unfounded beliefs with reasoned conclusions using rational arguments based on scientific evidence, historical evidence and logical reasoning.

HVH strives to be a group of friendly individuals. We welcome new members, and want them to feel at home in a safe haven of fellowship. HVH strives to be a contributing member of the overall community of the Hudson Valley. We seek full participation in community events. We are willing to network in cooperative endeavors with other organizations. As we promote Humanist values, we will maintain a high regard for the right of others to hold opposing views. We will participate in the arena of ideas in an honest and respectful manner.

Since 1973 the Humanist Association of San Diego has been serving the needs of our Humanist Community. We host the best Saturday Night Discussion Group in San Diego, as well as monthly lectures, and renown authors and speakers. We have promoted the separation of Church and State from fighting the Soledad Cross to standing with Scouting For All. We took to the streets and City Council to promote marriage equality against religious bigotry during Prop 8. We also retain the services of a certified Humanist Celebrant for Weddings, Memorials, and other rites of passage rituals. If you like fighting for civil rights, whale watching, or just keeping up to date on the cutting edge of the Free Thought movement come and join us!

HAGP is an educational and philosophical organization. Our main goal is to educate the general public about the ethics and values of Humanism by being a positive influence in the community. We do this through our meetings and lectures (free to the public); community service, networking encouraging debates and humanistic activities, and continuing our efforts through letter-writing, dialogue and other educational means to maintain the Jeffersonian "wall of separation" between church and state.
Humanist Association of Las Vegas and Southern Nevada

HALVASON, a chapter of the American Humanist Association, is a nonprofit, educational organization whose main purpose is to promote humanism as a viable alternative to supernatural and theistic belief systems. We serve as a forum for humanists, atheists, agnostics, freethinkers and other like-minded individuals in the Las Vegas area. We promote the Jeffersonian principle of separation of religion and government, the rights of nonreligious people in our society, free inquiry and thought, a naturalistic view of the universe and a reason-based, secular ethical system. Our membership is open to all like-minded people without regard to race, age, gender, sexual orientation, physical disability, or political or other affiliations.
Humanist Association of London and Area
We are a group of people from southwestern Ontario, Canada, who share the view that humans can live a meaningful, ethical, and joyful life without belief in religion or the supernatural.

The Humanist Association of Los Angeles serves Humanists and the public in the Southern California area, holding educational meetings open to the public, and discussing science, democracy, separation of church and state, and vital public issues.

Asimov Humanists is an atheist, agnostic, humanist and freethinker community in the Montgomery County, Texas, area, including The Woodlands, Conroe, Spring and North Houston. We invite all humanists, freethinkers, agnostics, atheists, and anyone else to join us for our monthly meetings to discuss current events from a secular viewpoint.

The Humanist Association of Orange County (HAOC) is a chapter of the American Humanist Association. Our purpose is to promote ethical, naturalistic, democratic humanism among our members and in our community.

The Humanist Association of Ottawa (HAO) has been operating since 1968. Members meet to discuss issues of morality and science, striving to ground morality in reason and compassion. The founding members insisted from the beginning that the HAO, like Humanist Canada, should be more than just a discussion group. Members of the HAO have been active in supporting a number of humanist causes over the years. The HAO has been supportive of a number of initiatives in Canada including the LGBT rights movement, the freedom of women to access abortion services if that is their choice, and the need for evidence to inform public policy.
Humanist Association of the Greater Sacramento Area (HAGSA)
HAGSA is a Chapter of the American Humanist Association. Its purpose is to promote ethical, naturalistic, democratic Humanism among our members and in our community.
The Humanist Association of Toronto (HAT) is an independent, non-profit, charitable organization. We promote Secular Humanism and the separation of church and state.

The Humanist Association of Tulsa is for people who are interested in a rational philosophy, informed by science, inspired by art, and motivated by compassion. The Humanist Association of Tulsa affirms the dignity of each human being, it supports the maximization of individual liberty, and opportunity consonant with social and planetary responsibility.
Humanist Association of West Central Florida
We are a 501C(3) non-profit educational organization, a chartered Chapter of the American Humanist Association and an affiliate of the Council for Secular Humanism.

Humanist Chaplaincy at American University is a chapter and grant recipient of the American Humanist Association comprised of AU students, faculty, and staff who come together to explore Humanism, to put into action its progressive values and insights, to celebrate all that is good in this life in this world, and to serve the University, the wider community, and the world.
The Humanist Chaplaincy at Rutgers University aims to create a vibrant Humanist community for Rutgers students, faculty, staff, alumni and their families.

Our meetings are very informal and wide-open for discussion on topics of current interest. Additionally, speakers, tapes and other materials are made available through AHA, The Humanists of Florida, and other sources to provide the basis for discussion.

Humanist Fellowship of San Diego While encouraging the advancement of Humanist philosophy and principles, we like to stretch your minds and your smiles! We are dedicated to providing interesting educational and social events for adults and families that will promote critical thinking, the pursuit of justice, personal acts of compassion, and community service. Our Humanist Chaplain is available to assist with celebrations and memorials.
Meet others who are interested in getting in shape and taking advantage of the beautiful hiking trails that are so close to us. We will meet one or two times a month at varying locations!
meet local humanist and amateur philosophers for stimulating conversation and friendship
HJCC is a local, emerging community newly founded in April, 2009. Our guiding philosophy is rooted in Humanistic Judaism.
The Humanist Society of Redding advocates a naturalistic approach to life and strives to make the world a better place.
Humanist Round Table of South Illinois, Carbondale Unitarian Fellowship
Humanist Round Table of South Illinois, Carbondale Unitarian Fellowship

We believe the scientific method, though imperfect, is still the most reliable way of understanding the world. Hence, we look to the natural, biological, social, and behavioral sciences for knowledge of the universe and man\'s place within it. We deplore efforts to denigrate human intelligence, to seek to explain the world in supernatural terms, and to look outside of nature for salvation. We appreciate the great benefits that science and technology (especially basic and applied research) can bring to humankind, but we also recognize the need to balance scientific and technological advances with cultural explorations in art, music, and literature.
Humanist Society of Greater Phoenix, HSGP

HSGP is a warm and welcoming community of humanists, atheists, agnostics, free-thinkers, and non-theists of all stripes. The group aims to enrich the lives of any who join us through explorations in science, philosophy, history, and the arts.
We are primarily an educational organization, providing bi-monthly lectures by experts in various fields; opportunities for intellectual discourse over books, arts, and specific discussion topics; and social events such as game nights, potlucks, and special celebrations through the year. Our members have diverse and passionate interests in topics such as separation of church and state, evolution, technology, and environmental issues.
We offer a community of secular minded people who want to spend time with like-minded individuals in a non-religious setting. Though we do not (yet) provide childcare at HSGP events, we do have a playroom and a family bathroom available, so parents are welcome to bring their children. Please consider joining us, for events that interest you, or as a member of our growing community.
Humanist Society of Metropolitan New York: The Corliss Lamont Chapter
The Humanist Society of Metropolitan New York (HSMNY) is one of many local chapters of the American Humanist Association (AHA).

The Humanist Society of Monroe - Michigan is a local community of people having a strong interest in or concern for human welfare, values, and dignity that is being formed to provide nonreligious people with the same opportunity for social interaction and community involvement that is often only available in religious societies.

The Humanist Society of New Mexico is a 501(c)(3) non-profit educational organization based in Albuquerque, New Mexico and is a chapter of the American Humanist Association. We are also affiliated with the Council for Secular Humanism at the Center for Inquiry.
We at the Humanist Society of Santa Barbara share the conviction that rational inquiry can provide the best foundation for human progress.
Meet other local Humanists, people who believe in the basic potential for goodness in humanity without supernaturalism.

Though many of our participants are affiliated with one of the Unitarian Universalist congregations in the greater Madison area, we are open to all humanists regardless of such affiliation or lack thereof. We are affiliated with the American Humanist Association.
Humanistic Jewish Havurah of Southwest Florida

Humanistic Jewish Havurah (HJH) is a voice for Jews who value their Jewish identity and who seek an alternative to conventional Judaism. Humanistic Judaism affirms the right of individuals to shape their own lives independent of supernatural authority.
Humanists and Freethinkers of Cape Fear

Humanists & Freethinkers of Cape Fear began meeting in 2005. They are a vibrant chapter of the American Humanist Association, focusing on social and community educational activities. They meet on the 2nd Sunday of each month a discussion or lecture, followed by a social hour with a pot luck supper. They also have several social events each year, such as: picnics, a Winter Solstice party, and other family friendly events.
Humanists and Freethinkers of New Bern

We are a non-profit, secular group of atheists, agnostics, skeptics, freethinkers, humanists, non-theists, and non-believers - pick whichever label you like best. We are a chapter of the American Humanist Association.

Humanists at UIUC provides a space for atheists, atheists+, agnostics, secular humanists, and other secular students to explore the scientific, ethical, and social issues facing modern humanism. We aim to focus our attention on the potential of humanism.

Humanists Doing Good is a community of compassionate and rational individuals centered in Grand Junction, Colorado. Our members and volunteers seek to do good deeds for the sake of doing good and without strings attached.

Our community is a chapter of the American Humanist Association. Our goal is to meet the social, intellectual, and emotional needs of humanists of all ages. We hold several weekly events, including a Sunday morning Forum with a different speaker speaking on a different topic each week, a Sunday morning family program for families with children, and a Sunday brunch after these two Sunday events.

The Humanists of BU are a collection of freethinking, inquisitive people who embrace skepticism while rejecting dogmatism. We are attempting to create a welcoming place for the nonreligious person on campus, but we also extend an offer to the religious person to join us in exploring morality and building a community of empathetic and interesting students.
The Humanists of Fort Worth is a Humanist organization for non-theists, freethinkers, and agnostics in the greater Cowtown area.
We are a secular community in the Portland Oregon area. We accept humanist values as a way to lead meaningful lives and to contribute to the well-being of society.

Humanists are informed by science, inspired by art, and motivated by compassion. Humanism stands for building a more humane society through an ethic based on human values in the spirit of reason and free inquiry. It is not theistic, and it does not accept supernatural views of reality. HOH was founded in 1978 as a home for Houston Humanists and to further Humanist values locally.
The Gathering of Secular Humanists is a progressive Humainst group dedicated to promoting positive Humanism.

Meet other local Humanists, people who believe in the basic goodness of the human spirit and that the best way to live your life is by the use of reason, critical thinking, empathy, compassion and real-world knowledge.
A gathering of people who support Humanism as the philosophy of living.

HNPS is a non-profit educational organization committed to positive social change through advocacy and education. We focus on issues relating to the separation of church & state, the importance of a secular democracy, human rights, environmental sustainability and peaceful solutions to global problems.

The Humanists of San Antonio provides intellectual social opportunities to fellow humanists. Our sponsor; the Freethinkers Association of Central Texas (FACT), conducts educational seminars at the Radius Center at least once monthly. We encourage members to submit ideas on topics and recommend speakers, to provide ideas for smaller discussion group topics and venues for meetings.

Humanism is a naturalistic philosophy that rejects all supernaturalism and relies primarily upon reason, science, democracy, and human compassion. Our mission is to advance our community through rational thought and expanding knowledge.
Humanists of the San Joaquin Valley

The Humanists of the San Joaquin Valley (HSJV) are people in the Central Valley who believe that people hold the key to making life better for people. We tend to seek progress based on reason and logic, without relying on supernatural explanations or motivations. We join together to become better people than we could be alone. We appreciate the fellowship and comfort of similarly-minded folk, and channel the strength of togetherness to forge a positive, critical, moral, fun, and productive community.
Humanists of the Sarasota Bay Area

We are a nonprofit corporation created to foster a community of freethinkers, dedicated to improving the human condition through rational inquiry, creative thinking, and appropriate action. HUSBAY serves mostly social and intellectual interests. The lectures have stimulated and enlightened us while the lunches have provided discussion and fellowship. The organization provides a haven for those who seek to find others they can share their secular orientation with and with whom they can feel a camaraderie and a relief from the sectarian world. We expect to continue to provide a port in the storm for anyone who shares our values, and we hope to contribute to a more rational and just world.

We strive to bring about a progressive society where being "good without god" is an accepted way to live life. We are accomplishing this through our defense of civil liberties and secular governance, by our outreach to the growing number of people without religious belief or preference, and through a continued refinement and advancement of the humanist worldview.

We are building a supportive community of humanist oriented adults and families who strive to be ethical but are not traditionally religious. We believe in social justice and compassion guided by reason. While we find no evidence to support a belief in the supernatural, heaven or hell, we do find evidence to support the benefits and the necessity of practicing the Golden Rule of treating others as we would like to be treated.

Meet other local Humanists. We are people who believe in the potential of human reason and compassion without supernaturalism. Humanists affirm the principles of democracy, scientific inquiry, and ethical human values.
Humanists of Utah, founded in 1991, is a chapter of the American Humanist Association. We are a non-profit corporation organized to advocate humanism among our membership and the larger community.
Meet other local Humanists, people who believe in the basic goodness of human nature without supernaturalism.

We are a Membership Chapter of the American Humanist Association. Humanism is a progressive philosophy of life that, without theism and other supernatural beliefs, affirms our ability and responsibility to lead ethical lives of personal fulfillment that aspire to the greater good of humanity.

The Ethical Humanist Society welcomes people from many different backgrounds and traditions. Whether you call yourself a Humanist, Free Thinker, a Bright, an Atheist, an Agnostic, a Pastafarian or want no label at all you are welcome to join us.

Humanity On Call Humanity On Call is a program of the Humanist Fellowship of San Diego dedicated to helping less fortunate San Diegans. Our projects express the values of Humanism in a concrete and compassionate fashion. If you possess the heart and the desire to reach out and make a difference in your community, JOIN US!, and impact the lives of your neighbors.
The Idaho Society of Reason (IDASOR) encourages rationale and logic over superstition.
Our friendly group represents humanists, skeptics, agnostics, Brights and atheists from northern Illinois and southern Wisconsin.

The Illini Secular Student Alliance is the campus group for nonreligious students at the University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign; providing a community while promoting science, skepticism and secularism by hosting speakers and special events throughout the year.

The Independent Investigations Group DC (IIG DC) investigates fringe science, paranormal and extraordinary claims from a rational, scientific viewpoint, and disseminates factual information about such inquiries to the public.
We hold monthly meetings in an informal and friendly atmosphere where we encourage and support each others search for truth in a world that seems increasingly hostile to free thought.

The Individuals for Free-thought (IF) is a student founded, student run organization on the Texas A&M University-Corpus Christi (TAMU-CC) campus. The group was established in 2010 and its mission is to provide a social environment for secular free-thinking students. Among a sea of religious organizations on the TAMU-CC, campus IF proved a safe-haven for like-minded students to host events, volunteer in the community and socialize with one another. The Individuals for Free-thought still flourishes today and is made up of students who identify themselves as skeptics, atheists, agnostics, secularists and above all, free-thinkers.

Informed by Nature organizes group trips to cool science events in the LA area. Whether its a star party at the Griffith Park Observatory, a talk at JPL, or a first Friday social event at the Natural History Museum, we meet up and go together, as a collection of people who love science, and often go out for a drink or coffee afterward. Ultimately, we hope to create a social community that emphasizes raising consciousness to the magnificence of the natural world and supporting the science that drives human progress.
Inland Empire Atheists, Agnostics and Skeptics

Inland Empire Atheists, Agnostics and Skeptics was founded in Riverside, California in 2006 as a community for freethinkers. We welcome atheists, agnostics, skeptics, brights, secular humanists and other freethinkers from all areas of the Inland Empire. Our goals are to educate the public about the positive values of non-theism, to encourage critical thinking in all aspects of our lives, to promote the separation of religion and government, and to provide support to non-believers who are having difficulty in declaring their life stance. Our group provides a sense of community to our members through a monthly meeting and a wide variety of social events.
Intellectual Cafe is a gathering of well-read individuals who go the extra mile in understanding the deep meaning behind issues concerning some citizens or the society as a whole.
This group is for YOU, if you want or are interested in the ENQUIRY.

Iowa Atheists and Freethinkers, Inc. (IAF) is a non-profit social and educational group working to provide a community of support and friendship for atheists, freethinkers, secular humanists, agnostics, and other non-religious people. IAF provides educational events; is active in community service projects; conducts charitable donation drives; and provides an environment where non-believers can be themselves.

The mission of AAS is to provide an educational and support system for students who believe that one can live a fulfilling, productive, and ethical life without religion. We promote civil discussion and would like to be seen as good citizens of our university and broader community.
The Jacksonville Atheists Meetup (JAM) was established as a safe haven for Jacksonville area atheists to come together and be among like-minded people.

The Jersey Shore Freethought Society is a community based organization of self-declared freethinkers assembling together for social support and grassroots activism in the New Jersey shore region of the United States.
The JCSS, an affiliate of the Congress of Secular Jewish Organizations, is dedicated to the study and celebration of Jewish history and culture within the philosophy of Secular Humanistic Judaism.
JMU Freethinkers, James Madison University Freethinkers

Freethinkers is a group that focuses on encouraging the value of secularism in open discussion and works to minimize the effects of prejudice and partisanship on discussions regarding controversial topics. As a group, we hope to build a community that will be united not by the content of our personal beliefs, but by our common vision that every thought must be freely expressed in order to have an informed opinion about the people that we share the world with. We meet once a week to discuss topics ranging from religion to politics to society and culture.
Helping people connect who have left religion or are leaving.
A group of freethinkers, atheists, humanists, skeptics, secularists, Unitarian Universalists, non-believers, and "others" in the Jonesboro, Arkansas area.

We hold that beliefs should be formed on the basis of science and logic rather than emotion, authority, tradition or dogma. We advocate the use of reason, defend the separation of church and state and support human rights, civil rights, tolerance and equality for all. Our goal is to provide a social and intellectual community for those who promote these principles. Mission Statement: To represent, organize, and unite the secular citizens of southwest Missouri by promoting the ideals of rationality.
Kahal Am - The Humanistic Jewish Community of San Diego

Kahal Am is a compelling option for modern Jewish identity in the San Diego Area. Humanistic Jews understand Judaism as the human-centered history, culture, civilization, ethical values, and shared experiences of the Jewish people. We believe that individuals shape their own lives independent of a supernatural authority. You may recognize that our humanistic views of Jewish culture, traditions, and observances correspond with the way in which you would like to cherish your Judaism. Our warm, caring community welcomes anyone who identifies with Judaism, including intercultural families.
Kahal B\'raira, Boston Congregation for Humanistic Judaism
Humanistic Judaism offers an alternative approach to Judaism, including non-theistic celebrations of Jewish holidays and life-cycle events and a love of Jewish heritage.

This group was created as a place for Atheists, Agnostics, Freethinkers, Skeptics, and Humanists in the Charleston area to meet and socialize in a friendly, supportive environment. The purpose of this group is to help non-religious people create and develop a part of their social lives that is free of religious pressure, and to provide an outlet to discuss the non-religious aspects of our lives.
Kansas City Free Thought - Wyandotte & Leavenworth County

Come to our meetup for Wyandotte and Leavenworth atheists, agnostics, humanists, secularists, and other godless heathens! We meet monthly and chat about whatever, many of us attend other events all over town.
Kansas City Free Thought, KC Freethinkers

Kansas City Free Thought is designed to provide news with a local slant relevant to free thinkers and links to local and other relevant free thought web sites. While designed for free thinkers, hopefully others will find it of interest.
Kansas City FreeThinkers Social Group - Overland Park

This meetup group is for free-thinking adults who are interested in getting together for general social activities - conversation, dining, drinking, dancing, picnics, hiking, whatever we think of. We welcome anyone with an interest in getting out and participating in fun activities with like-minded individuals. We keep a full calendar of activities and are always open to suggestions.

We tend to be atheists, agnostics, humanists and secularists although people of faith are welcome to join us in our lively discussions of how freethought can counter dogma and promote a realistic, healthy, and compassionate world view.

Do you enjoy rational discussion, logic, and learning? What about hanging out with like-minded people who also enjoy these things? Questioning what we are told is an incredible attribute that humans have and we should exercise it by encouraging critical thought! Anyone is welcome to join, but this group is intended for those who want to question dogma and learn from others, while having fun with people who do the same.

This is a group for smart, critically thinking women who enjoy a mix of quality conversation as well as paltry celebrity gossip. At any given event, conversation easily vacillates between weighty social issues, to tawdry sex talk, to esoteric philosophic discussion, to bitching about our significant others and sharing fun mom stories. We\'re basically just a bunch of fun, cool chicks who like to kick back a bottle of wine on a Thursday night whenever given the opportunity.
The Kent State Freethinkers were founded in Fall of 2008 to give a voice to those that stand up for science and reason.
Kingwood Humble Atascocita Atheists is a group of non-believers serving the NE Houston area including Kingwood, Humble, Atascocita, and Porter.

This group is for all of the atheists, rationalists, humanists and/or non-believers in the West Sound. This is a group for open-minded people to get together and talk about their views of the world, recent news, philosophy, or whatever interests them, without worrying that their lack of belief will be an issue.
A social organization dedicated to education and the promotion of critical thinking, science and skepticism.
Tired of feeling like you are on a Island with no one to talk to. Purpose of group. Support anything Non-Theist. Who should join? Atheist, Humanist, Skeptics, and of course freethinkers.

Kol Hadash Humanistic Congregation is the only full-service Humanistic Jewish congregation in the Chicago area. As a result, we draw members from Chicago to Libertyville and Gurnee, from Naperville to Deerfield and Highland Park.
Kol Hadash, Northern California Community for Humanistic Judaism

Kol Hadash ("New Voice" in Hebrew) was organized in 1987 as the Northern California Chapter of the Society for Humanistic Judaism, by a handful of individuals who were looking for a way to celebrate their cultural Jewish identity nontheistically.
Kol Haskalah, A Humanistic Jewish Congregation
Kol Haskalah, A Humanistic Jewish Congregation
Kol Haverim, The Finger Lakes Community for Humanistic Judaism
Kol Haverim is a secular Jewish congregation in Ithaca, NY for those who desire non-theistic ways to celebrate their identity, culture and heritage.
Kol Shalom, Community for Humanistic Judaism
An affiliate of the national Society for Humanistic Judaism. We celebrate Jewish culture and tradition non-theistically.

The La Crosse Area Freethought Society (LCAFS) is a local forum in which nontheists can meet, socialize, and exchange ideas. Our mission is to promote positive freethought, the separation of church and state, and the application of reason and science to human understanding.

We are an atheist, agnostic, freethinkers, humanist, etc social group for lively discussion and perhaps a bit more. Anything is open for discussion at our meetings. Meetings are varied in different settings and some are family friendly (a coffeeshop or a library) and other meetings are simple bar nights.

This is a group for the atheists, secularists, and humanists of Camp Pendleton. We want to promote a positive view of atheists, etc. in the military and let people know that foxhole atheists do exist.

As we all know, the military life can be strenuous and difficult, especially at times of deployment. As a military spouse and sibling, I’m aware of the different resources the military has for these families. However, a small number of us are still not entirely being accommodated. There are plenty of support groups whose aim is to console the spouses and other family members that are left behind while their loved ones are deployed, but they all tend to rely on their religious practices. The local support groups on and off post, though well meaning, tend to focus a lot (if not entirely) on spirituality. As freethinkers, it is difficult for us to find things like prayer, or bible study sessions, helpful in these situations. It’s logical that, even though we know his or her intentions may be good, someone encouraging us to pray is not necessarily consoling. So I’m creating this group in hopes that those other wives, family members, or soldiers, who are in the same situation will have a place to vent and discuss their worries without the need for prayer. Conversing with like-minded people in the same situation can be helpful and I hope it can do the same for others during deployment.
